      • getUniqueID

        public java.lang.Object getUniqueID(javax.swing.tree.TreePath path)
        Description copied from interface: Identifiable
        Returns an unique identifier for the specified path if applicable. This method is usually used to store a tree state on disposing, so we cannot use invoker to calculate it later on a valid thread, and an implementor must be ready to support any thread.
        Specified by:
        getUniqueID in interface Identifiable
        Parameters:
        path - a tree path in the current tree model
        Returns:
        an unique identifier for the specified path, or null if not applicable
        See Also:
